Obviously, that wasn't the case. The monster let out a deafening roar and tried to charge straight at Sazalin. Luckily, Sazalin, despite its massive size, was agile enough to dodge it. However, Nisi still couldn't help but scream, and she almost slipped off Sazalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Target their heads!"
"It's too hard!"
Sasarin let out a snarl, circled around once, and flew towards the mountain he called home. The black creature was hot on its heels, but when it was hit from behind by flames, it looked a bit disoriented. This creature hadn't yet realized it had another opponent. Sasarin slowed down, then used his tail to deliver a powerful swipe to the creature's head, sending it off course, and the creature grew even more frantic.
The monster let out a deafening roar, its throat producing a screeching sound as it flew straight up, spewing something from its mouth into the air. Suddenly, the surroundings grew pitch-black, as if the monster was sucking in the sky's light and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasarin's vision blurred, and he tried to retreat, but he crashed into a tree branch and fell to the empty ground. The monster seemed to know exactly where Sasarin had landed, flew straight towards him, and took the dark cloud with it.
"Kael!" Tenuk shouted as he flew out of the cloud, beginning to circle and try to find Nisi and Sasarin in the darkness below. "What do we do? Kael...? Kael, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to her feet, feeling that she was undoubtedly broken in half, but her strange, unnatural healing ability was already taking effect. Sasarin's situation was different, lying powerless on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked over. Nisi struggled to make her way to Sasarin, but her vision was a solid black, and she could hardly see anything. Everywhere there were terrifying shadows, and something was screaming in the shadows.
A terrifying club-like tail slammed into the ground, sending Nisi tumbling to the ground. She noticed that the tail was flailing wildly, but it seemed the target was not her. Nisi barely made out that the monster was bellowing, frantically scratching at the shadows it had created with its claws. Something darted through the darkness, poised to strike at the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot rang out, silencing the monster instantly as it fell to the ground motionless. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kael stood on the monster's lifeless body, a rifle in hand, panting heavily.
"That was... this was one of the strangest shadow leaps I've ever done... Tantu Catelon...". Kael gasped for air, saying this. For some reason, his eyes were flashing with black light, and a dark energy was surging through his body. But just as Kael began to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
It took Nisi a while to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kael possessed the ability to manipulate shadows in a strange way, but he rarely used this ability because most people considered it to be very evil and terrifying. However, Nisi didn't know that Kael could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kael's reaction, he seemed to be just as surprised as Nisi.
"Nisi couldn't help but ask, 'Are you okay?'"
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon." Kael looked at his handiwork, and then Tenuk landed beside him, returning to its normal Spaster form.
Now that the creature is no longer moving, they can take a closer look at what it is. Its dark, glossy skin is covered in a thick, sticky liquid that clings tightly to its body. It has four wings and four legs, with long, slender claws at the end of each leg. Two straight horns protrude from its skull.
Tenuk and Kael hadn't even had time to wonder what this thing was when another creature shrieked out of the nearby thicket. Just then, a familiar car crashed into the creature's side, and the creature slid to a stop at Nisi's feet. Nisi didn't hesitate, grabbing her shotgun and firing a shot directly at the creature's head, killing it instantly.
"Ah, oh...," Rethvik muttered from the driver's seat, then clumsily killed the engine and climbed down from the truck. "Uh, it wasn't on purpose. You all okay?"
"Tenuk clicked his tongue in dismay, saying, 'You missed all the action!' 'Where did you run off to?'"
"Ah, you left me behind," Rethvik sighed, "I've been trying my best to catch up... Please tell me, what are these terrifying things?"
Rethvik's questions were answered by Sasarin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looked a bit dazed but seemed to be faring relatively well.
"You killed the Corrupter! Those infected creatures. When Corruption strikes at your gods, these beings are left behind here."
"You're saying... we... helped kill the terrifying Tantu Catelon?" Tenuk stuttered.
"Yes, indeed. There may be more Corrupters out there. But I couldn't just shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it wouldn't be fair, one on two, would it?" Sasarin approached Kael, rapping him on the head. "Thanks, kid. You remind me of my old friend Alcardin. Only you're not as vicious, and you don't have his destructive power to destroy the universe."
"Ah... thanks... I think... so, um, did we complete the mission?"
Nisi shrugged, picked up her camera, and snapped a few photos of the confirmed-dead creatures. Then, she pulled out her favorite knife – that exquisite Reaper Knife – and began to slice off one of the creatures' horns, before moving on to the other. However, just as Nisi finished cutting, the creatures suddenly burst into flames, quickly turning to ash. The horn she had cut off also reduced to ash.
"I guess it's a double-edged sword... at least I still have my photos."
